 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Senior Scientist - REMOTE: Europe Indica Labs Albuquerque, NM 87114 Remote Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Senior Scientist 
 
Deep learning and Computational Pathology 
 
Classification: FLSA Exempt (US Only) 
 
Reports To: Principal Scientist,  Deep Learning and Computational Pathology 
Special Note: Our corporate headquarters is located in Albuquerque, New Mexico, USA. This position is a remote position, eligible to any candidate who currently resides in Europe, with appropriate authorisation to work in their home country. 
Summary 
 
This is a scientific and technical position responsible for performing scientific analysis on digital pathology images with appropriate presentation of key data to the stakeholders. The successful candidate is expected to manage projects independently and liaise directly with external collaborators to ensure the timely and quality delivery of products. 
 
 
Duties and Responsibilities 
 
 Performs end-to-end histo-pathology image analysis studies on projects involving Indica Labsâ€™ clinical and academic collaborators. 
 Meets with collaborators to identify study requirements and propose study design. 
 Conducts image analysis tasks using Indica Labâ€™s suite of software on digital pathology images; including image annotations, applying multiple image analysis and AI algorithms, and data analysis. 
 Maintains regular status communications with collaborators and Indica Labs team throughout a studyâ€™s execution. 
 Prepares study reports for internal and external projects and present results, data, and findings. 
 Independently manages artificial intelligence-based image analysis projects with external collaborators, including working with managers, software teams, and collaborators to ensure the project adheres to timelines and set deliverables.
 Oversees data transfer and management between Indica Labs and external collaborators. 
 Creates documentation to ensure algorithm development follows set quality framework management guidelines to fast-track regulatory approval and clinical translation. 
 Responsible for the appropriate accessing and handling of electronic Protected Health Information (PHI) as outlined by policy and the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). 
 Assists in the write-up of scientific publications and scientific abstracts and posters for conference presentation. 
 This job description is not designed to cover or contain a comprehensive listing of activities, duties, or responsibilities that are required of the employee. Duties, responsibilities, and activities may change, or new ones may be assigned at any time with or without notice. 
 
 
